cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper deals with object recognition in images and range images using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the challenges of domain shift and the need for efficient learning methods, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes a Siamese CNN architecture, which is commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) for tasks such as visual odometry and object tracking. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which is a common concern in neural network optimization (cs.NE).
